=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_FilterComparisons_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 331 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and impulsive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, and filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: impulsive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: moderate
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 330.5801
  harmonic_decay_rate: -5.0619
  harmonic_regularity: 0.2473
  pitch_clarity: 35.7183
  inharmonicity: 0.2857
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -20.2815
  resonance_freq: 279.9316

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Filter Comparisons Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/FilterComparisons.html
// Tags: FilterComparisons, Guides, filter
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
{ Streson.ar(LFSaw.ar([220, 180], 0, mul:EnvGen.kr(Env.asr(0.5, 1, 0.02), 1.0) * 0.2), LinExp.kr(LFCub.kr(0.1, 0.5*pi), -1, 1, 280, 377).reciprocal, 0.9, 0.3) }.play
